h3cDlswExt.name: h3cDlswExt

revisions.description: Initial version of this MIB module.

h3cDlswExt.contactinfo: R&D Beijing Huawei-3com Technologies Co., Ltd. Oriental Electronic Bld., NO.1, Street 8, Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District, Beijing, P.R. China Zip:100085 Http://www.huawei-3com.com E-mail:support@huawei-3com.com
h3cDlswExt.description: The MIB module for management of HUAWEI-3COM specific Data Link Switching protocol enhancements. DLSw is described in RFC 1795, RFC 2024 and RFC2166.

h3cdeNodeVendorID.name: h3cdeNodeVendorID
h3cdeNodeVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of this DLSw. This information is reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

h3cdeNodeIpAddrType.name: h3cdeNodeIpAddrType
h3cdeNodeIpAddrType.description: The type of ip address: IPv4 or IPv6.

h3cdeNodeLocalAddr.name: h3cdeNodeLocalAddr
h3cdeNodeLocalAddr.description: Local peer ip address. This ip address must have been configured for a port on the router. If no local peer ip address is configured, then this object will be the empty string.

h3cdeNodePriority.name: h3cdeNodePriority
h3cdeNodePriority.description: Peer priority advertised to remote peers in the DLSw Capabilities Exchange. If an end station can reach through more than one peer, the priority of each peer will be considered when a circuit is established. A lower priority indicates that peer will be the preferred choice if there are more than one path to the destination. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

h3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow.name: h3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow
h3cdeNodeInitPacingWindow.description: Initial pacing window size. This is the starting size of the pacing window. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

h3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.name: h3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow
h3cdeNodeMaxPacingWindow.description: Maximum pacing window size. This is the largest size that the pacing window will grow to. DLSw uses an adaptive pacing flow control algorithm that automatically adjusts to congestion levels in the network. Pacing windows are used to control how many packets may be sent to a peer before acknowlegement.

h3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.name: h3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval
h3cdeNodeKeepAliveInterval.description: Default remote peer keepalive interval in seconds. The keepalive parameter refers to how often DLSw peers send peer keep alives to each other. These periodic messages allow DLSw to keep track of the state of all peers. If set to zero, no keepalives are sent. A value of 65535 indicates the value is meaningless.

h3cdeNodePermitDynamic.name: h3cdeNodePermitDynamic
h3cdeNodePermitDynamic.description: To accept connections from non-configured remote peer when permitDynamic is specified.

h3cdeNodeConfigSapList.name: h3cdeNodeConfigSapList
h3cdeNodeConfigSapList.description: The SAP list indicates which SAPs are allowed. Only SAPs with even numbers are represented, in the form of the most significant bit of the first octet representing the SAP 0, the next most significant bit representing the SAP 2, to the least significant bit of the last octet representing the SAP 254. Data link switching is allowed for those SAPs which have one in its corresponding bit, not allowed otherwise. The whole SAP list has to be changed together. Changing the SAP list affects only new circuit establishments and has no effect on established circuits. This list can be used to restrict specific partners from knowing about all the SAPs used by DLSw on all its interfaces (these are represented in h3cdeIfSapList for each interface). For instance, one may want to run NetBIOS with some partners but not others. If a node supports sending run-time capabilities exchange messages, changes to this object should cause that action. When to start the run-time capabilities exchange is implementation-specific. The DEFVAL below indicates support for SAPs 0, 2, 4, 6, 8, A, C and E.

h3cdeNodeMaxTransmission.name: h3cdeNodeMaxTransmission
h3cdeNodeMaxTransmission.description: The maximum retry times for TCP packet. Default value is 5.

h3cdeNodeMulticastStatus.name: h3cdeNodeMulticastStatus
h3cdeNodeMulticastStatus.description: Multicast support status. It is disabled by default.

h3cdeNodeMulticastAddress.name: h3cdeNodeMulticastAddress
h3cdeNodeMulticastAddress.description: Multicast address. Default is 224.0.10.0. When the h3cdeNodeMulticastStatus is disabled, the multicast address is reset to 0.0.0.0.

h3cdeNodeResetTcpAll.name: h3cdeNodeResetTcpAll
h3cdeNodeResetTcpAll.description: Reset all TCP circuit switch. Any return value is meaningless.

h3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum.name: h3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum
h3cdeNodeStCapTcpNum.description: Tcp number reported in DLSw Capabilities Exchange.

h3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax.name: h3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax
h3cdeNodeTcpQueueMax.description: The max length of TCP queue.

h3cdeTConnConfigTable.name: h3cdeTConnConfigTable
h3cdeTConnConfigTable.description: This table defines the peer transport connections that will be initiated or accepted by this DLSw. This table augments dlswTConnConfigTable.

h3cdeTConnConfigEntry.name: h3cdeTConnConfigEntry
h3cdeTConnConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection.

h3cdeTConnConfigVersion.name: h3cdeTConnConfigVersion
h3cdeTConnConfigVersion.description: This value identifies which version (first octet) and release (second octet) of the DLSw standard is supported by this partner DLSw. This information is obtained from a DLSw Capabilities Exchange message received from the partner DLSw. A string of zero length is returned before a Capabilities Exchange message is received, or if one is never received. A conceptual row with a h3cdeTConnOperState of 'connected' but a zero length partner version indicates that the partner is a non-standard DLSw partner. If an implementation chooses to keep h3cdeTConnOperEntrys in the 'disconnected' state, this value should remain unchanged.

h3cdeTConnConfigBackup.name: h3cdeTConnConfigBackup
h3cdeTConnConfigBackup.description: The current remote peer is configured as the backup of another configured remote peer.

h3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.name: h3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr
h3cdeTConnConfigBackupTAddr.description: It is the ip address of a configured remote peer of which the current remote peer is configrued as backup.

h3cdeTConnOperTable.name: h3cdeTConnOperTable
h3cdeTConnOperTable.description: A list of peer transport connections. Each connected peer will create a conceptual row in the table. When the peer disconnects, the row will be deleted from the table. This table augments dlswTConnOperTable.

h3cdeTConnOperEntry.name: h3cdeTConnOperEntry
h3cdeTConnOperEntry.description: A list of objects that contain spefific operational information for a DLSw peer transport connection.

h3cdeTConnOperPeerType.name: h3cdeTConnOperPeerType
h3cdeTConnOperPeerType.description: The current remote peer is configured when the value is 'configured'.

h3cdeTConnOperVendorID.name: h3cdeTConnOperVendorID
h3cdeTConnOperVendorID.description: The value identifies the manufacturer's IEEE-assigned Organizationally Unique Identifier (OUI) of remote peer.

h3cdeTConnOperVersionString.name: h3cdeTConnOperVersionString
h3cdeTConnOperVersionString.description: Version information of remote peer. The length up to 512 bytes.

h3cdeTConnOperUpTime.name: h3cdeTConnOperUpTime
h3cdeTConnOperUpTime.description: The amount of time (in seconds) since this transport connection last entered the 'connected' state.

h3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.name: h3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress
h3cdeTConnOperMulticastAddress.description: When remote peer supports DLSw2.0, this node identifies its multicast address.

h3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.name: h3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber
h3cdeTConnOperStCapTcpNumber.description: Number of tcp supported when capabilities exchanging.

h3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts.name: h3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts
h3cdeTConnOperRecvPkts.description: The number of Switch-to-Switch Protocol (SSP) messages received on this tcp transport connection.

h3cdeTConnOperSendPkts.name: h3cdeTConnOperSendPkts
h3cdeTConnOperSendPkts.description: The number of SSP messages sent on this tcp transport connection.

h3cdeTConnOperDropPkts.name: h3cdeTConnOperDropPkts
h3cdeTConnOperDropPkts.description: The number of SSP messages dropped on this tcp transport connection.

h3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable.name: h3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable
h3cdeTConnTcpConfigTable.description: This table defines the TCP transport connections that will be either initiated by or accepted by this DSLw. It augments the entries in dlswTConnConfigTable whose domain is dlswTCPDomain. In other words for each conceptual row in the dlswTConnConfigTable, if the dlswTConnConfigTDomain is dlswTCPDomain, that conceptual row will be augmented by this table. dlswTCPDomain, dlswTConnConfigTable, and dlswTConnConfigTDomain are all imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024). This table augments dlswTConnTcpConfigTable.

h3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.name: h3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry
h3cdeTConnTcpConfigEntry.description: A list of objects that define specific configuration for a DLSw peer transport connection within the dlswTCPDomain. dlswTCPDomain is imported from DLSW-MIB (RFC 2024).

h3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.name: h3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax
h3cdeTConnTcpConfigQueueMax.description: Maximum output TCP queue size for this remote peer. For DLSw over TCP encapsulation, packets may be queued due to congestion of the TCP network. This variable is used to set the output queue maximum of the underlying TCP connection for the peer represented by the conceptual row.

h3cdeBridgeTable.name: h3cdeBridgeTable
h3cdeBridgeTable.description: A list of bridge group which is serving for DLSw.

h3cdeBridgeNumIndex.name: h3cdeBridgeNumIndex
h3cdeBridgeNumIndex.description: This value identifies the bridge number.

h3cdeBridgeIfTable.name: h3cdeBridgeIfTable
h3cdeBridgeIfTable.description: The list of interface on which DLSw is active.

h3cdeBridgeIfEntry.name: h3cdeBridgeIfEntry
h3cdeBridgeIfEntry.description: The list of bridge interface information.

h3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.name: h3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp
h3cdeBridgeIfBrgGrp.description: This value identifies the bridge number attached to the interface.

h3cdeQllcTable.name: h3cdeQllcTable
h3cdeQllcTable.description: The table defines attributes related for those QLLC that participate in data link switching.

h3cdeQllcEntry.name: h3cdeQllcEntry
h3cdeQllcEntry.description: The ifIndex belongs to the interface which link protocol is x.25.

h3cQllcLocalMac.name: h3cQllcLocalMac
h3cQllcLocalMac.description: The virtual MAC address used to represent the QLLC-attached link station to the rest of the DLSw network.

h3cQllcLocalSap.name: h3cQllcLocalSap
h3cQllcLocalSap.description: The SAP used to represent this link station.

h3cQllcRemoteMac.name: h3cQllcRemoteMac
h3cQllcRemoteMac.description: The MAC address to which DLSw should attempt to connect this link station. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

h3cQllcRemoteSap.name: h3cQllcRemoteSap
h3cQllcRemoteSap.description: The SAP of the remote station to which this link station should be connected. If this information is not available, a length of zero for this object should be returned.

h3cdeSdlcPortTable.name: h3cdeSdlcPortTable
h3cdeSdlcPortTable.description: The table defines parameters for the interfaces whose link protocol is SDLC.

h3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.name: h3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission
h3cdeSdlcPortMaxTransmission.description: Number of times to retry an operation.

h3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK.name: h3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK
h3cdeSdlcPortTimerACK.description: Time to wait for a reply to a frame.

h3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.name: h3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime
h3cdeSdlcPortTimerLifeTime.description: Time to wait for a reply used by secondary station.

h3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.name: h3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause
h3cdeSdlcPortTimerPollPause.description: Time between polls for each secondary SDLC station.

h3cdeLlc2PortTable.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTable
h3cdeLlc2PortTable.description: This table defines parameters for the Ethernet interface.

h3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck.name: h3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck
h3cdeLlc2PortMaxAck.description: Maximum of I-frames received before ACK.

h3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.name: h3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow
h3cdeLlc2PortReceiveWindow.description: Maximum number of I-frames to send before received ACK.

h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck
h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAck.description: Waiting for ACK time after sending an I-frame.

h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay
h3cdeLlc2PortTimerAckDelay.description: Maximum time allows I-frames incoming without replay ACK.

h3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy
h3cdeLlc2PortTimerBusy.description: Waiting time while other LLC2 station is in busy state.

h3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll
h3cdeLlc2PortTimerPoll.description: Waiting time after a P frame is sent.

h3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject.name: h3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject
h3cdeLlc2PortTimerReject.description: Waiting time after a REJ frame is sent.

h3cdeRchCacheNextIndex.name: h3cdeRchCacheNextIndex
h3cdeRchCacheNextIndex.description: The next value of h3cdeRchCacheIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in h3cdeRchCacheTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC address cache, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

h3cdeRchCacheStatus.name: h3cdeRchCacheStatus
h3cdeRchCacheStatus.description: Current status of reachable cache entry.

h3cdeRchCacheRemainTime.name: h3cdeRchCacheRemainTime
h3cdeRchCacheRemainTime.description: Remain time of reachable cache entry.

h3cdeRchCacheMac.name: h3cdeRchCacheMac
h3cdeRchCacheMac.description: MAC address of reachable cache entry.

h3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp.name: h3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp
h3cdeRchCacheRemoteIp.description: Remote peer ip address of reachable cache entry.

h3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex.name: h3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex
h3cdeEBMacMapNextIndex.description: The next value of h3cdeEBMacMapIndex to be assigned by the agent. A retrieval of this object atomically reserves the returned value for use by the manager to create a row in h3cdeEBMacMapTable. This makes it possible for the agent to control the index space of the MAC mapping tables, yet allows the manager to administratively create new rows.

h3cdeEBIfTable.name: h3cdeEBIfTable
h3cdeEBIfTable.description: Information of interface which works for DLSw Ethernet redundancy.

h3cdeEBIfEntry.name: h3cdeEBIfEntry
h3cdeEBIfEntry.description: Parameters defined for DLSw Ethernet redundancy interface.

h3cdeEBMulticastMac.name: h3cdeEBMulticastMac
h3cdeEBMulticastMac.description: Multicast MAC address configured for the Ethernet redundancy of dlsw module. When Ethernet redundancy is inactive, its value is '000000000000'H. To active Ethernet redundancy, give it a valid multicast MAC address.

h3cdeEBPriority.name: h3cdeEBPriority
h3cdeEBPriority.description: Priority configured for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

h3cdeEBtimer.name: h3cdeEBtimer
h3cdeEBtimer.description: Timer for the Ethernet redundancy of DLSw module.

h3cdeEBMacMapIndex.name: h3cdeEBMacMapIndex
h3cdeEBMacMapIndex.description: Index of MAC address mapping entry.

h3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac.name: h3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac
h3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac.description: Local MAC address in MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, h3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac and h3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

h3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.name: h3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac
h3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac.description: Remote MAC address of MAC address mapping. When creating a new conceptual row, h3cdeEBMacMapLocalMac and h3cdeEBMacMapRemoteMac should be set simultaneously.

h3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus.name: h3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus
h3cdeEBMacMapRowStatus.description: Status of MAC address mapping entry.
